{"questionId":"26602","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A college runs a mathematics course in the morning. Scores for a test from this class are&nbsp;shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>33</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>51</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>62</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>63</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>63</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>74</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>79</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>79</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>81</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>88</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>98</mn></math></p>\n<p>For these data, the lower quartile is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>62</mn></math> and the upper quartile is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>88</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the test score of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn></math> would not be considered an outlier.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>88</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>62</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>26</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;seen anywhere&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn></math>&nbsp;seen anywhere&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>62</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>39</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>23</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>23</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so is not an outlier&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26602","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ2.7a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the test score of 25 would not be considered an outlier.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.1—Concepts, reliability and sampling techniques"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}